==English==
=== Adjective ===
'''autochthonous''' ''or'' '''autochthonal''', '''autochthonic'''
# [[native]] to the place where [[found]]; [[indigenous]]
# ([[biology]], [[medicine]]) [[originating]] where found



=== Pronunciation ===

aw-täk-thuh-nuhs

=== Noun ===
'''autochthonism''' ''or'' '''autochthony'''
# the condition of being autochthonic

=== Adverb ===
'''autochthonously'''
# in an autochthonous manner

=== Information ===
Autochthonous was the winning word of David Tidmarsh in the 2004 Scripps National Spelling Bee.